      <p>Mesa Alamosa is a smaller version of Landergin Mesa some five miles to 
        the east, and is sometimes called &#8220;Little Landergin Mesa.&#8221; 
        It, too, may be a defensive retreat position used by Antelope Creek villagers 
        during periods when hostile raids were expected. Mesa Alamosa was known 
        to Studer and Hughes, but was first formally recorded by Marmaduke and 
        Whitsett in 1973. Photo by Chris Lintz. </p>
